{"sha": "ffa31d235badfb5544ddb2de151ccfc66c8a20e6", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmZmYTMxZDIzNWJhZGZiNTU0NGRkYjJkZTE1MWNjZmM2NmM4YTIwZTY=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "gifnksm", "email": "makoto.nksm+github@gmail.com", "date": "2013-04-29T02:53:01Z"}, "committer": {"name": "gifnksm", "email": "makoto.nksm+github@gmail.com", "date": "2013-04-29T04:49:27Z"}, "message": "libstd: modify wrong shift width.\n\nborrow = *elem << (uint::bits - n_bits);\n\nThe code above contains a bug that the value of the right operand of the shift operator exceeds the size of the left operand,\nbecause sizeof(*elem) == 32, and 0 <= n_bits < 32 in 64bit architecture.\n\nIf `--opt-level` option is not given to rustc, the code above runs as if the right operand is `(uint::bits - n_bits) % 32`,\nbut if --opt-level is given, `borrow` is always zero.\n\nI wonder why this bug is not catched in the libstd's testsuite (I try the `rustc --test --opt-level=2 bigint.rs` before fixing the bug,\nbut the unittest passes normally.)", "tree": {"sha": "977283606f18bc2c776add3622314daa53edb67b", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/977283606f18bc2c776add3622314daa53edb67b"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/ffa31d235badfb5544ddb2de151ccfc66c8a20e6", "comment_count": 5, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/ffa31d235badfb5544ddb2de151ccfc66c8a20e6", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/ffa31d235badfb5544ddb2de151ccfc66c8a20e6", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/ffa31d235badfb5544ddb2de151ccfc66c8a20e6/comments", "author": {"login": "gifnksm", "id": 164213, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2NDIxMw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/164213?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/gifnksm", "html_url": "https://github.com/gifnksm", "followers_url": 